Summary: a small Cantonese style restaurant with traditional favorites! Highly recommend their rice clay pot casseroles! So yummy and so cheap! Seating is limited, take out recommended. Might only take cash, not sure.  I came here to order take out as my in-laws recommended their rice clay pot casseroles. I haven't had rice clay pots since I was younger and was very excited to order. We ordered 2 beef and poached egg pots, 1 beef navel pot, and 1 frog pot. Cook time on a busy Thanksgiving afternoon took about 20 minutes (which is pretty impressive considering the full dining area and packed take out area). Even with take out, they still give you the clay pots and you just pay an extra $2 deposit fee. You can keep the clay pots or you can return them with your receipt another day to get your $2 back. Since this was my first time there and I know Clay pots are definitely more expensive elsewhere, I chose to keep mine. Having this rice clay pot meal reminded me of my childhood when my father used to cook it often. Thanks King's kitchen for the throwback!  Not sure if they take credit cards, we paid in cash. No parking, good luck finding street parking on weekends and holidays. It can be intimidating walking into the restaurant and ordering take out because it seems like everyone speaks just Chinese but they do speak English too so don't be shy!
